{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17622876","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17622876"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:06:18+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:06:18+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16827"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16827","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16827"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.13,0.25,0.25,0.21,0.17]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9518"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76657"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9518","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9518"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16827"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62154"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22484"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22489"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76657","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76657"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe arteria radicularis magna provides the main blood supply to the anterior spinal cord in the thoracolumbar region. Its location is important to identify before thoracoabdominal surgery.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the most common anatomical origin of the arteria radicularis magna?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Right side at T8 level","Left side at T9 level","Right side at T9 level","Left side at T10 level","Right side at T10 level"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe arteria radicularis magna, also known as the artery of Adamkiewicz, is a critical vessel that provides the main blood supply to the anterior two-thirds of the lower thoracic and lumbar spinal cord. Understanding its anatomy is crucial for surgeons performing procedures involving the thoracoabdominal aorta.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeft side at T9 level\u003C/strong\u003E is the most common location for the origin of the arteria radicularis magna. It arises from a posterior intercostal artery on the left side in approximately 75% of people, typically between T9 and T12, with T9 being the most common level.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERight side at T8 level\u003C/strong\u003E is an uncommon location for this vessel. While the artery can occasionally arise from the right side (in about 25% of cases), T8 would be an unusually high origin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERight side at T9 level\u003C/strong\u003E is possible but less common than a left-sided origin. When the vessel does arise from the right side, it typically occurs at a similar vertebral level as left-sided variants.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELeft side at T10 level\u003C/strong\u003E, while possible, is less common than T9. However, this would still be within the typical range of T9-T12 for a left-sided origin.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERight side at T10 level\u003C/strong\u003E is an uncommon anatomical variant, as right-sided origins occur in only about 25% of cases.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIdentification of this vessel is particularly important before thoracoabdominal surgery to prevent postoperative paraplegia from spinal cord ischaemia. Modern imaging techniques, including computed tomography angiography, can help identify the location of this important vessel preoperatively.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The arteria radicularis magna (artery of Adamkiewicz) typically arises from the left side between T9-T12 in 75% of people.","The arteria radicularis magna is the main blood supply to the anterior spinal cord in the thoracolumbar region.","Knowledge of this vessel\u0027s anatomy is crucial for thoracoabdominal surgery to prevent spinal cord ischaemia."],"references":["Hasan S, Arain A. Neuroanatomy, Spinal Cord Arteries. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK539889/","Howard, R., Kullmann, D., Werring, D., \u0026 Zandi, M. (Eds.). (2024). Neurology: a queen square textbook. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62154"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16827"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62154","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62154"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T20:24:00+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T20:26:04+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9518"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76657"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"descript